@adriancole 
Almost done.
Could you please try to use it?

@openzipkin/elasticsearch does anyone know how to work around an error like this when a write sneaks in before the index template finishes initialization? There's some eventual consistency issue that leads to this. Ex a GET succeed while a PUT is in progress on another host or before it applied. When that passes a POST can be written without the template, poisoning the index. This is the hyphothesis as in a case where this happened we noticed the index template is actually correct.

